{"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/glibobject\/object\/takeref()"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/Object","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/Object\/ObjectProtocol-Implementations"]]},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/Object\/takeRef()"},"abstract":[{"text":"If ","type":"text"},{"code":"object","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is floating, sink it.  Otherwise, do nothing.","type":"text"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"takeRef","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"() -> "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:10GLibObject0B3RefV","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/ObjectRef","text":"ObjectRef","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":"!","kind":"text"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"anchor":"discussion","type":"heading","text":"Discussion"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In other words, this function will convert a floating reference (if"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"present) into a full reference."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Typically you want to use ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_object_ref_sink()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" in order to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"automatically do the correct thing with respect to floating or","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"non-floating references, but there is one specific scenario where","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"this function is helpful.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The situation where this function is helpful is when creating an API","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"that allows the user to provide a callback function that returns a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"GObject. We certainly want to allow the user the flexibility to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"return a non-floating reference from this callback (for the case"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"where the object that is being returned already exists).","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"At the same time, the API style of some popular GObject-based","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"libraries (such as Gtk) make it likely that for newly-created GObject","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"instances, the user can be saved some typing if they are allowed to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"return a floating reference."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Using this function on the return value of the user’s callback allows","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the user to do whichever is more convenient for them. The caller will","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"always receives exactly one full reference to the value: either the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"one that was returned in the first place, or a floating reference","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"that has been converted to a full reference.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This function has an odd interaction when combined with"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_object_ref_sink()"},{"text":" running at the same time in another thread on","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the same "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/Object"},{"text":" instance. If ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_object_ref_sink()"},{"text":" runs first then","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the result will be that the floating reference is converted to a hard"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"reference. If "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_object_take_ref()"},{"text":" runs first then the result will be","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"that the floating reference is converted to a hard reference and an","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"additional reference on top of that one is added. It is best to avoid"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"this situation."}]}]}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"sections":[],"metadata":{"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"takeRef"},{"kind":"text","text":"() -> "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:10GLibObject0B3RefV","text":"ObjectRef","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"!"}],"role":"symbol","title":"takeRef()","roleHeading":"Instance Method","modules":[{"name":"GLibObject"}],"externalID":"s:10GLibObject0B8ProtocolPAAE7takeRefAA0bE0VSgyF::SYNTHESIZED::s:10GLibObject0B0C","symbolKind":"method","extendedModule":"GLibObject"},"kind":"symbol","references":{"doc://GLibObject/documentation/GLibObject/Object/takeRef()":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/Object\/takeRef()","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"takeRef"},{"kind":"text","text":"() -> "},{"text":"ObjectRef","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:10GLibObject0B3RefV"},{"text":"!","kind":"text"}],"title":"takeRef()","url":"\/documentation\/glibobject\/object\/takeref()","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"If "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"object"},{"type":"text","text":" is floating, sink it.  Otherwise, do nothing."}]},"doc://GLibObject/documentation/GLibObject/Object":{"title":"Object","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Object","kind":"identifier"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"Object","kind":"identifier"}],"kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/glibobject\/object","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/Object","type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The base object type."}],"role":"symbol"},"doc://GLibObject/documentation/GLibObject/Object/ObjectProtocol-Implementations":{"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/Object\/ObjectProtocol-Implementations","title":"ObjectProtocol Implementations","url":"\/documentation\/glibobject\/object\/objectprotocol-implementations","abstract":[],"kind":"article","role":"collectionGroup"},"doc://GLibObject/documentation/GLibObject":{"role":"collection","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject","abstract":[],"title":"GLibObject","kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/glibobject"},"doc://GLibObject/documentation/GLibObject/ObjectRef":{"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/ObjectRef","fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"ObjectRef","kind":"identifier"}],"url":"\/documentation\/glibobject\/objectref","kind":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"ObjectRef","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The base object type."}],"role":"symbol","title":"ObjectRef"}}}